{
  "texts": [
    "CF-based trackers are the most widely-applied framework, and the results differ such that the trackers based on original CF methods (DMKCF, DSKCF, and DSOH) perform significantly worse than those developed on improved CF (OTR, WCO, and TACF).",
    "OTOD based on point cloud does not exploit the effectiveness of CNN and attains the 10th rank on the PTB dataset.",
    "Attribute-based comparisonPTB provides 11 attributes and five features for comparison.",
    "CF-based trackers, including OTR, WCO, TACF, CSR-RGBD, and CCF, do not perform well in tracking animals.",
    "As animal movements are fast and irregular, these online trackers are fragile to drift."
  ]
}